---
import EventLayout from "../../components/EventLayout.astro";

const images = [
  { src: "/ai-hackathon-i/4.jpeg", alt: "AI Hackathon I" },
  { src: "/ai-hackathon-i/2.jpeg", alt: "AI Hackathon I" },
  { src: "/ai-hackathon-i/1.png", alt: "AI Hackathon I" },
  { src: "/ai-hackathon-i/3.jpeg", alt: "AI Hackathon I" },
];
---

<EventLayout
  title="AI Hackathon I"
  date="March 8, 2025"
  location="The Beacon, Antwerp"
  type="Hackathon"
  description="14 teams. One day. The first North Star Agentic Hackathon - where multi-agent systems met real-world problems."
  images={images}
>
  <p>The first edition set the tone for everything that followed. Fourteen teams showed up on a Saturday morning and built agentic AI systems from scratch - financial analysis tools, codebase stress-testers, research agents that filter papers by credibility.</p>
  <p>Three winners emerged across Tech, Creativity, and AI's Choice categories. The winning projects ranged from a multi-agent financial analysis swarm to an AI research agent that cross-references ArXiv with social media discussions.</p>
  <p>Special thanks to <strong>Ken Casier</strong> for the closing keynote and <strong>The Beacon</strong> for hosting us in their space.</p>
</EventLayout>
